Heritage day should not be seen as a mere holiday and a day off school or work, it should be an opportunity to embrace your cultural norms, values and traditions. The day was declared a holiday during the late former president Nelson Mandela’s tenure. It is a day where South Africans can embrace their diversity and use it to come together and teach one another about their different culture. Many South Africans will be spending this day reflecting on their heritage and identity. If that is not reason enough for you to celebrate this day, here are a few more reasons why you should embrace this national holiday. 1. You get to learn about other people’s culture. 2. You get to wear your traditional clothes 2. It’s a good excuse to have a braai with friends and family. 3. You get to visit some exciting heritage sites. ALSO READ: WATCH: HERITAGE SITES AROUND THE WORLD!